{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\nReconcile infra/terraform-github with the live GitHub mirror-lock and make the lock's\ndeploy-key existence gate FAIL-CLOSED. The lock was applied via gh-api during WS7 (ruleset\ngerrit-mirror-lock-main, id 18402431); Terraform state is empty and the module still defines a\ntag_lock we deliberately did NOT apply (main-only cutover).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] infra/terraform-github/main.tf is MAIN-ONLY: the tag_lock resource + its output are removed\n      (tags stay human-pushable so release.yml v* pushes keep working).\n- [ ] The check \"deploy_key_present\" block is replaced by a lifecycle { precondition } on the\n      main_lock resource so a MISSING replication deploy key ABORTS apply (fail-closed), not just WARNs.\n- [ ] Stale comments reconciled: the deleted legacy ruleset was id 18306946 (not 18048287); note the\n      main-only decision.\n- [ ] Live reconcile: terraform import of the live ruleset (rebar:18402431) into main_lock, then\n      terraform plan reports \"No changes\" against live GitHub.\n- [ ] terraform validate passes; a contractual test asserts the config is main-only + has the\n      precondition (no tag_lock).\n\n## Files\n- infra/terraform-github/main.tf"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782946249017878001,"uuid":"de8045a2-0897-4567-8e41-c1db1dceb5d9"}